Source: I004 and `docs/superpowers/plans/2026-07-17-visible-quota-configuration.md`, Task 2.

Add the private built-in catalogue/editor document and public `configuration({persisted,event})` projection for set, provider reset, and reset-all events. Reuse the runtime decoder/identity/default model; preserve no-write inspection, current edit-time legacy/global materialisation, unknown per-provider keys, and compatible deterministic JSON.

Acceptance: exact provider/window labels, order, and defaults are tested; explicit `QuotaParsers` fixtures prove every built-in canonical ID/default agrees while labels may intentionally differ and dynamic IDs remain runtime-authoritative; first edits seed/materialise current semantics; invalid advanced text remains untouched on inspection; provider/reset-all behaviour is explicit; unknown keys survive unrelated edits; event output is deterministic and repeating the same event is idempotent.
